HEADWORD: Durion
<hw>Du"ri*on</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The fruit of
the durio. It is oval or globular, and eight or ten inches long. It has
a hard prickly rind, containing a soft, cream-colored pulp, of a most
delicious flavor and a very offensive odor. The seeds are roasted and
eaten like chestnuts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

